import React, { useEffect, useState } from "react"; import axios from "axios"; export const AnalysisTab = () => { const [data, setData] = useState({ costPerUnit: 0, marketRevenue: 0, expenses: 0, dailyVisits: 0, costPerUnitChange: 0, marketRevenueChange: 0, expensesChange: 0, dailyVisitsChange: 0, highestSaleYear: 0, highestSaleCount: 0, highestEvCity: "", highestEvCount: 0, highestExpenseYear: 0, highestExpenseAmount: 0, predictedSales2030: 0, }); useEffect(() => { const fetchData = async () => { try { const response = await axios.get( "http://localhost:5000/api/ev-analysis" ); setData(response.data); } catch (error) { console.error("Error fetching data", error); } }; fetchData(); }, []); return (
{/* Highest Sales Year */}
